CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER - RUSSIA: (MOSKOVSKAYA)
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Fri 23 Nov 2007
Source: OIE WAHID animal disease interface [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=6502>


Classical swine fever, Russia
-----------------------------
Information received on 23 Nov 2007 from Mr.
Evgueny A. Nepoklonov, Deputy Head, Orlikov per.,
1/11, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, MOSCOW, Russia

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 10 Oct 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 06 Nov 2007
Report date: 23 Nov 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 23 Nov 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2005
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Classical swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: Defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak Location: MOSKOVSKAYA OBLAST
("Lotoshinskaya Okhota," Savostino village)
Total animals affected
Species: Wild species
Susceptible: NA
Cases:4
Deaths:0
Destroyed:4

Epidemiology
Source of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Hunting is prohibited.
Neighbouring districts (Volokolamskiy,
Istrinskiy) were not free from classical swine fever in 2005-2006.

Control measures
Measures already applied:
- Screening
- Quarantine
- Control of wildlife reservoirs
- Zoning
- Vaccination permitted
- No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied:
None specified

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Federal Centre for
Animal Health (FGI-ARRIAH), Yur'evets, Vladimir (National laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species: Wild species
Tests
1. Enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA)
Test date: 06 Nov 2007
Result: Positive
2. Nucleotide sequencing
Test date: 06 Nov 2007
Result: Positive
3. Reverse transcription Â­ polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date: 06 Nov 2007
Result: Positive

--
Communicated by:
OIE animal health information department
<oie-info-web@oie.int>

[This is Russia's 5th notification on outbreaks
of CSF during 2007; the 4 previous notifications
were located in various parts of Russia, from the
far east to western Russia (in brackets, number
of outbreaks): Krasnodar (1), Volgograd (1),
Stavropol (2), and Primorsky (1). In difference
with current outbreaks, involving wild boars, all
the previous 5 outbreaks involved farmed domestic pigs.

Data of all 2007's notifications, with maps, are available at
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=country_reports>. - Mod.AS]
